|{{flag|Austria}}||&lt;!-- start date --&gt;||See [[Austria–Chile relations]]

The first bilateral relations dates back from 1846. Austria has an embassy in [[Santiago de Chile]] and 3 honorary consulates (in [[Arica, Chile|Arica]], [[Valdivia, Chile|Valdivia]] and [[Valparaíso]]). Chile has an embassy in [[Vienna]] and 3 honorary consulates (in [[Linz]], [[Klagenfurt]] and [[Salzburg]]). 
