|{{flag|Croatia }}||&lt;!-- start date --&gt; 1992-04-15
||See [[Chile–Croatia relations]]
* Chile has an [[embassy]] in [[Zagreb]] and [[honorary consulate]]s in [[Rijeka]] and [[Split (city)|Split]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.echile.hr/ Chilean embassy in Zagreb]&lt;/ref&gt;
* Croatia has an embassy in [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]] and honorary consulates in [[Antofagasta]] and [[Punta Arenas, Chile|Punta Arenas]].
* The [[Senate of Chile]] has awarded [[President of Croatia|Croatian President]] [[Stjepan Mesić]] an order of merit, to honor the improvement of bilateral relations between Croatia and Chile. While representing Chile, senate vice president Baldo Prokurica stated that he found areas for stronger collaboration in future in oil and gas research and shipyards and he expressed an interest in Chilean students' having scholarships in Croatia.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web |url=http://www.javno.com/en-croatia/president-mesic-receives-order-of-merit-from-chile_164808 |title=President Mesić Receives Order Of Merit From Chile |date=2008-07-16 |accessdate=2009-04-15 |work=[[HINA]] |publisher=Javno.hr}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* There are between 380,000 and 500,000 people of [[Croats|Croatian descent]] living in Chile.
* [http://www.mvpei.hr/CustomPages/Static/HRV//templates/_frt_bilateralni_odnosi_po_drzavama_en.asp?id=71 Croatian Ministry of Foreign Affairs and European Integration: list of bilateral treaties with Chile]
