|{{flag|Finland }}||&lt;!-- start date --&gt;1931||See [[Chile–Finland relations]]

Chile recognised Finland's independence on June 17, 1919. Diplomatic relations between them were established in 1931 and have been continuously maintained, despite pressures at times to discontinue them.&lt;ref name=&quot;historia&quot;&gt;{{Cite web | url = http://www.finland.cl/public/default.aspx?nodeid=36916&amp;contentlan=9&amp;culture=es-ES | title = La historia de las relaciones entre Finlandia y Chile |  date = 2008-02-22 | accessdate = 2009-05-06 | language = Spanish | publisher = Embajada de Finlandia, Santiago de Chile }}&lt;/ref&gt; The two countries maintain resident ambassadors in both capitals.&lt;ref name=&quot;historia&quot; /&gt;
