===Israel===
{{Main|Chile–Israel relations}}

Chile recognized Israel's independence in February 1949.&lt;ref name =chileanembassy&gt;{{cite web |title=Bilateral Relationship Chile -  Israel |publisher=Embassy of Chile in Israel |date= |url=http://www.embachile.org.il/bilateral.htm |accessdate=2009-04-15}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref name = israeliembassy&gt;{{cite web |title=Relaciones Bilaterales: Revisión Histórica ''(Bilateral Relations: Historical Review)'' |publisher=Israeli Embassy in Chile |url=http://santiago.mfa.gov.il/mfm/web/main/document.asp?SubjectID=2010&amp;MissionID=16&amp;LanguageID=510&amp;StatusID=0&amp;DocumentID=-1 |accessdate=2009-04-15 |language=Spanish}}&lt;/ref&gt; Both countries established diplomatic relation on 16 May 1950, with Israel sending their first ambassador on that date and Chile sending their first ambassador on 16 June 1952.&lt;ref name = chileanembassy /&gt;  Chile has an embassy in [[Tel Aviv]].&lt;ref name = chileanembassy /&gt;  Israel has an embassy in [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]].&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web |title=General Info: Mission Details |publisher=Israeli Embassy in Chile |date= |url=http://santiago.mfa.gov.il/mfm/web/main/document.asp?SubjectID=1010&amp;MissionID=16&amp;LanguageID=0&amp;StatusID=0&amp;DocumentID=-1 |accessdate=2009-04-15}}&lt;/ref&gt;

