The '''National Armed Forces of Côte d'Ivoire''' ({{lang-fr|Forces armées nationales de Côte d'Ivoire}}; '''FANCI''') are the [[armed forces]] of [[Côte d'Ivoire]] (Ivory Coast). It is headed by the chief of staff and commander of the FANCI.

==Army==
===Organization===
In 1987 [[Côte d'Ivoire]] was divided into five military regions, each commanded by a [[colonel]]:&lt;ref&gt;[[Library of Congress]], [http://www.country-data.com/cgi-bin/query/r-7024.html Cote d'Ivoire Country Study], circa 1987, accessed January 2009&lt;/ref&gt;

* '''First Military Region''' - The army had the majority of its forces concentrated in and around [[Abidjan]], its principal units there being a rapid intervention [[battalion]] (airborne), an [[infantry]] battalion, an armored battalion, and an air defense [[artillery]] battalion.
* '''Second Military Region''' - Located in [[Daloa]] and is assigned one infantry battalion.
* '''Third Military Region''' - Headquartered in [[Bouaké]] and home to an artillery, an infantry, and an engineer battalion (currently controlled by [[Forces Nouvelles de Côte d'Ivoire|FN forces]]).
* '''Fourth Military Region''' - Maintained only a Territorial Defense Company headquartered in [[Korhogo]] (currently controlled by [[Forces Nouvelles de Côte d'Ivoire|FN forces]]).
* '''Fifth Military Region''' - Formerly known as the Western Operational Zone, a temporary command created to respond to the security threat caused by the [[Liberian Civil War]].

===Equipment===
*[[T-55]] [[main battle tank]] x10 {{USSR}}
*[[AMX-13]] [[light tank]] x5 {{flag|France}}
*[[BRDM-2]] [[Armored car (military)|armored car]] x13 {{USSR}}
*[[Mamba APC]] x10 {{flag|South Africa}}
*[[BTR-80]] [[armoured personnel carrier]] x6 {{flag|Russia}}
*[[Panhard AML]] [[Armored car (military)|armored car]] x16 (8x AML-90 + 8x AML-60) {{flag|France}}
*[[Panhard M3]] APC {{flag|France}}
*[[Véhicule de l'Avant Blindé]] (VAB) [[armoured personnel carrier]] x13 {{flag|France}}
*[[ACMAT]] (VBLA) {{flag|France}}
*[[ERC 90 Sagaie]] x7 {{flag|France}}
*[[BMP-1]] [[infantry fighting vehicle]] x13 {{USSR}}
*[[M-46]] 130mm field gun {{USSR}}
*[[M102 howitzer|M102]] 105mm towed howitzer x4 {{USA}}
*Brandt M-50 120mm heavy mortar {{flag|France}}
*[[M1 mortar|M1]] 81mm medium mortar {{USA}}
*[[Bofors 40 mm gun|Bofors 40mm towed anti-aircraft gun]] x5 {{flag|Sweden}}
*20mm anti-aircraft gun (type unknown) x14 {{flag|France}}
*[[Panhard M3]] VDA armored personnel carrier with 2x20mm anti-aircraft guns x6 {{flag|France}}
*[[RG-12]] armoured personnel carrier x5 {{flag|South Africa}}
*[[LRAC F1]] light anti-tank rocket launchers {{flag|France}}
*[[M40 recoilless rifle]] {{USA}}

==Gendarmerie==
The gendarmerie is roughly equivalent in size to the army. It is a national [[police]] force which is responsible for territorial security, especially in [[rural]] areas. In times of national crisis the gendarmerie could be used to reinforce the army. The gendarmerie is commanded by a [[colonel-major]] and comprises four Legions, each corresponding to one of the four numbered military regions, minus the temporary military operational zone on the western border.

==Navy==
Côte d'Ivoire has a [[brown-water navy]] whose mission is [[coast]]al surveillance and security for the nation's 340-mile coastline.

===Equipment===
* 1 Patra patrol craft - 147 tons full load - commissioned 1978
* 2 CTM LCM - 150t - commissioned 1968
* 2 Rodman 890 fishery protection - commissioned 1997

==Air Force==
The Air Force's official name, Ivoirian Air Transport and Liaison Group (''Groupement Aérien de Transport et de Liaison''--GATL), reflects an original mission focused more on logistics and transport rather than a combat force.&lt;ref&gt;http://www.country-data.com/cgi-bin/query/r-7024.html&lt;/ref&gt;

In 2004, following an [[2004 French–Ivorian clashes|air strikes on French peacekeepers]] by Ivorian forces, the French military destroyed all aircraft in the Air Force of Côte d'Ivoire, including two [[Sukhoi 25]] ground-attack aircraft and three [[Mil Mi-24]] helicopters.&lt;ref&gt;
{{cite news
 | title = Ivory Coast seethes after attack
 | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/3989127.stm
 | publisher = BBC News
 | date = [[2004-11-04]]
 | accessdate = 2007-10-10
 }}&lt;/ref&gt;

Since then, the Air Force of Côte d'Ivoire has been rebuilt.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news
 | title = Ivory Coast seethes after attack
 | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/3989127.stm
 | publisher = BBC News
 | date = 2004-11-04
 | accessdate = 2007-10-10
 }}&lt;/ref&gt;

===Equipment===
Since 2004, efforts to put together some form of inventory have led to possibly as many six aircraft being in service by the end of 2006. It is unknown whether any of these aircraft are truly operational.

