== International forces ==
===France===
A mutual defense accord signed with [[France]] in April 1961 provides for the stationing of [[Military of France|French forces]] in Côte d'Ivoire.&lt;ref&gt;Boubacar N'Diaye, 'Ivory Coast's Civilian Control Strategies 1961-68: A Critical Assessment,' Journal of Political and Military Sociology Special Issue on West Africa, Vol. 28, No. 2, Winter 2000, p.253&lt;/ref&gt; The 43rd [[French Marines|Marine]] Infantry Battalion is based in [[Port Bouet]] adjacent to the [[Abidjan Airport]] and has more than 500 troops assigned. The French military also maintains a force as part of [[Operation Licorne]].

===United Nations===
Currently the [[United Nations]] has the peacekeeping mission [[ONUCI]] in the country.

